1
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:12,000
This is Sua Krong.

2
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,360
She used to my one of my former girls.

3
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:16,400
I'm not gonna let you...

4
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,600
go again...

5
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:20,640
I don't wanna fly this flight!

6
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:24,040
There's a story going around about a haunted seat.

7
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,880
Someone died there.

8
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:27,760
I'm scared, Chai.

9
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:28,720
I'm not scared!

10
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:30,120
I wrote a ghost-scanning app, remember?

11
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:31,840
If this device detects a ghost,

12
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,760
it'll make a...

13
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,320
beep sound.

14
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:36,080
Yeah, just like that.

15
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:37,080
That was loud and clear.

16
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,440
Hey, hey, hey, Chaba!

17
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:13,800
Can you walk a bit more quietly?

18
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,600
I thought we were flying through some turbulence.

19
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:18,840
Chai, help me. I can't take this any longer.

20
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,400
What's wrong?

21
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:23,560
That passenger with the tiger-striped mask...

22
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:26,360
you know, kept asking for this and that...

23
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,000
to borrow, to take...

24
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:31,800
(song) "Can I hold this? Can I touch that? Don't get cheeky, baby."

25
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:34,040
If the passenger is asking for that much, you gotta be patient.

26
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:34,920
Why so?

27
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:37,200
Because we are service-minded, okay?

28
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,680
You got this. It's only one passenger.

29
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:41,120
Breathe in.

30
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,720
Breathe in, okay?

31
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:45,680
Smile. Let me see.

32
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:46,840
Ah, okay.

33
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,640
Smile one more time.

34
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:51,120
Smile, smile, smile, smile, smile.

35
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,960
Smile, smile, smile.

36
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:53,480
Smile, smile.

37
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:56,760
Hey, this is more tiring than providing service for that tiger-masked stripe passenger.

38
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,480
It's alright, trust me.

39
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:00,120
You gotta go for it.

40
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:02,120
Go for it, okay?

41
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:02,640
Go.

42
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:03,920
Alright, Chaba, you got this!

43
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:04,400
Keep smiling.

44
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,760
Keep smiling.

45
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,760
Tiger Mask, I'm back!

46
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:08,840
And walk quietly.

47
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:18,240
Chaba, calm down.

48
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,400
What's wrong?

49
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:23,080
Chai, can I ask you to get revenge for me?

50
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:27,040
That Tiger Mask is the pain in the ass.

51
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,360
Alright, Tiger Mask, right?

52
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:31,160
Yes, there's only one Tiger Mask on this plane.

53
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:34,160
You think you're gonna get away with this, Tiger Mask?

54
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,400
No one messes with my sis!

55
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:48,960
Excuse me, would you like anything else?

56
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:54,360
I'd like a hot tea.

57
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:56,680
And also, some soda.

58
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,640
Zero sugar, please.

59
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:00,160
Some water...

60
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:01,360
at room temperature, please.

61
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:03,960
I'm having a sore throat.

62
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:07,920
And a latte, less sweet.

63
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:10,560
Wait, not sweet at all...

64
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,560
And one mineral water, please.

65
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,360
Is that all, ma'am?

66
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,560
Yes.

67
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,120
She's way too much.

68
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:24,520
Will Chai be able to handle this?

69
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:26,920
But if he's smiling like that,

70
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:27,920
I'm sure he's alright.

71
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,160
I'm relieved now.

72
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,440
So is that all?

73
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:44,440
Yes, that is all.

74
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:56,880
Hey, is Chai getting in trouble?

75
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:57,880
Chai, I'm here!

76
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,680
So you're not getting in any kind of trouble?

77
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,440
No.

78
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,080
I'm just falling in love.

79
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:14,320
Here, let me introduce you, this is Sua Krong.

80
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,440
She's one of my former girls.

81
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:20,440
I'll handle this.

82
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,280
Sua Krong.

83
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,040
Yes?

84
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,040
Please follow me.

85
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:37,440
A person named Sua Krong?

86
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:39,520
That's a whole new level of tacky.

87
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,200
Are you alright?

88
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,320
Yes, I'm alright.

89
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,160
And you, Sua?

90
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,440
I'm okay.

91
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,240
You're okay?

92
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,120
I'm okay.

93
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:59,120
Okay, three, two, one...

94
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,840
Hey, what are you two doing?

95
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,080
My back is sore.

96
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:14,280
Sua Krong is a yoga instructor.

97
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,280
So she's helping me stretch.

98
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,720
Oh, I thought you two are...

99
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,720
doing it here.

100
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:21,840
Oh, no.

101
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,640
But why didn't you let me teach you yoga?

102
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:26,200
You know how to do it?

103
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,200
Yes, of course.

104
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,680
Alright, maybe next time.

105
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,560
Let me introduce you first.

106
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,520
This is Chaba.

107
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,560
I'm Chai's girlfriend.

108
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:39,360
Oh.

109
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,600
Hey, what's so funny?

110
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,920
Oh, nothing.

111
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:42,920
You're adorable.

112
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:47,320
I have to apologize for being a Karen earlier.

113
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:50,320
I just wanted this guy here to go take care of me.

114
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,040
Oh, that's alright.

115
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:55,520
But this area is for crew only.

116
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:59,520
It's alright, Chaba. I was the one who invited her.

117
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:03,360
I'll get back to my seat now, then.

118
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,600
Hello, I'm here too.

119
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:12,920
So are you alright?

120
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:14,640
Of course.

121
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:18,120
So what's the story?

122
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,680
Well, Sua was one of my former girls.

123
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:23,480
I'd been hitting on her for a long time.

124
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,240
But she never agreed to be my girlfriend.

125
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,040
Well, that must be her fate.

126
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:29,640
Seems like her sacred blessings haven't run out yet.

127
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:31,320
But tonight,

128
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:35,320
I'm not gonna let her go.

129
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,880
I'll follow her.

130
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:40,640
I'll get to see how she's doing.

131
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,840
I'll get to see what kind of moves she's got.

132
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:45,320
Go! Get it over with!

133
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:46,320
I'm so sick and tired of this.

134
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,320
(sigh)

135
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,040
(sigh)

136
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:55,640
(sigh)

137
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,200
Tid-Gift, what is it?

138
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,800
You were sighing the whole time.

139
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:03,280
Well, I don't wanna fly this flight.

140
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:04,680
Why not?

141
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:07,720
It's the new aircraft. And the flight crew are awesome.

142
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,240
There's nothing to worry about.

143
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:12,240
Or you don't like the destination?

144
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:16,800
Well, this aircraft...

145
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,160
there's a story...

146
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,160
Really?

147
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,040
What is it?

148
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:25,280
Well, I heard there's a haunted seat.

149
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:26,840
Huh?

150
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,920
Well...

151
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:32,240
There was this one couple. The girl loved seafood so much....

152
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:35,440
and she was preparing the prawns for the guy.

153
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,720
But the guy wouldn't eat them.

154
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:38,880
Because he was allergic to them.

155
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,440
So the girl asked for a breakup.

156
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:43,160
Just because he was allergic to prawns.

157
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:44,760
He was desperate.

158
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:47,960
So he flew back alone.

159
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:54,800
And while he was on the plane, he was crying the whole time.

160
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:03,920
And suddenly, he picked up 7 kilograms of prawns and started eating them.

161
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:15,320
After a while, rashes started spreading all over his body.

162
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:18,120
His eyes turned red, blood began seeping from them.

163
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,760
He was in absolute agony...

164
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:23,960
coughing violently until...

165
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:27,960
blood splattered all over the seat and then...

166
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:32,080
he died right there on the spot.

167
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,080
Hey!

168
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,520
All-New!

169
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:44,000
Sorry, I got bored so I turned off the lights.

170
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,680
You scared us!

171
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:46,680
What's wrong with you?

172
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,640
And after that flight...

173
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:54,280
that seat became haunted.

174
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:57,120
Ever since that flight, that seat has always been left empty.

175
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,200
It may be due to a booking error.

176
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:02,000
No, you can ask Sky or Chaba.

177
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,400
That's interesting.

178
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,360
Anything else?

179
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,840
Strange things have been happening.

180
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:09,040
Sometimes, there are unexplained sounds...

181
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:10,240
A faint smell...

182
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,680
A shadow that moves without anyone nearby...

183
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:13,680
And then...the crying...huh...

184
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,680
huh...huh...

185
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,480
All-New!

186
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,240
Sorry, I dropped the tray, I didn't mean to.

187
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,240
What?

188
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,600
What is wrong with you, All-New?

189
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,920
All-New, aren't you scared at all?

190
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,800
Ghosts aren't real.

191
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,080
There are only a few things in this world that are scary.

192
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,120
Computer viruses...

193
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:36,480
Losing battery chargers...

194
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:38,520
Or would you like me to write a code?

195
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,280
Use a ghost-scanning function,

196
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,640
maybe we'll actually detect something.

197
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:43,760
Better yet, a ghost-blocking function.

198
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,760
Just block the damn ghost altogether.

199
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,000
Wait a minute,

200
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,160
that's actually not a bad idea.

201
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:51,560
A ghost scanner app...

202
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:52,920
If I build it now,

203
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:55,480
I can test it on the haunted seat during the next flight.

204
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,920
So I can prove to these two...

205
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:00,920
that ghosts aren't real.

206
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:20,320
Hey, Chaba, where are you going?

207
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:22,600
Over there.

208
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:23,440
What?

209
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,800
I'm going to get there.

210
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:25,520
What was that again?

211
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,880
I'm flying another flight.

212
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:29,920
Oh, that haunted seat flight?

213
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:33,720
Right, Sky says if I fly with her, she will feel more relieved.

214
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,040
So I gotta hurry.

215
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:35,960
Alright, alright.

216
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:36,960
I'm off now.

217
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,080
What was that all about?

218
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:41,080
Chai.

219
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:43,960
Are you done for today?

220
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,720
Yes.

221
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:49,080
Get home safely.

222
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,120
Bye-bye.

223
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,200
Er, Sua Krong...

224
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:57,240
Will we ever get to see each other again?

225
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:58,520
That depends whether...

226
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,520
you'd still like to see me or not.

227
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:08,400
What if I'd like to ask for your number again?

228
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:15,240
Oh, you deleted my number?

229
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,600
Should I play hard to get?

230
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,520
Don't be so mean.

231
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:23,320
I lost my phone, that's why I don't have your number.

232
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:25,320
Please, may I have your number?

233
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,080
Here it is.

234
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:29,680
Thank you.

235
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:32,840
I'm still the same.

236
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:35,440
Nothing has changed.

237
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:38,360
You know what's still exactly the same?

238
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,360
We've still never been official, like, never actually been a couple.

239
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:45,320
Well, do you wanna change that?

240
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,600
Do you?

241
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:52,560
Let me think about it.

242
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:58,960
Er, Chai...

243
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:01,840
Can I ask you something first?

244
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:04,920
Will you say yes?

245
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:07,120
I'll say yes to anything.

246
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,800
I mean it.

247
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:12,200
Even if I'm exhausted from flying,

248
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,200
I'm still full of energy just for you.

249
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:18,480
You're still so sweet, just like always.

250
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,800
Of course.

251
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:23,800
Tell me what you want, anything at all.

252
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:27,880
Do you have, like...3,000 Baht in cash?

253
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:32,640
You want me to go buy condoms right now or...

254
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:35,880
wait, what?

255
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:37,520
Yes, 3,000.

256
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,800
I don't have toll money.

257
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:43,800
And was hoping to borrow some...is that okay?

258
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,640
Of course!

259
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:49,640
I've got 5,000, take it all.

260
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:53,200
Sky, this is Sua Krong.

261
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:55,320
3,000 Baht for toll money? What the hell!

262
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,080
Is she going to Okinawa or something?

263
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:01,400
That's true. I think she seems weird.

264
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:05,000
From her looks, I don't think she's a good person.

265
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:07,880
And Chai gave her money?

266
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:08,880
He's so easy to fool.

267
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:09,640
That's true.

268
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:12,200
But when it comes to us, he's stingy as hell.

269
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,040
Right, I gotta go fly now.

270
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:18,040
Wait, I'm flying with you. Wait for me!

271
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:22,800
Sua Krong, may I walk you to your car?

272
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,720
Oh, that's alright.

273
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:28,240
You've done so much for me already.

274
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,680
We'll grab dinner.

275
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:32,600
And I'll give your money back.

276
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,800
Thank you so much, Chai.

277
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:35,720
Oh?

278
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:38,560
We'll grab dinner and I'll give your money back.

279
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:40,640
Okay, of course.

280
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:40,960
Bye-bye.

281
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,120
Bye-bye.

282
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:49,080
What the hell is wrong with me?

283
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:50,440
My mouth's way too fast,

284
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:53,120
too honest too.

285
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,280
But hey, at least...

286
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:56,280
I got her number.

287
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:13,160
Where did you get those?

288
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:14,920
You're wearing so many amulets!

289
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:17,440
Someone got me these good stuff.

290
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:20,160
Damn, the vibe back here is creepy as hell.

291
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:22,920
The rear seats are almost empty.

292
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:25,000
That's good though. Less people, less work.

293
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,880
Don't be scared of ghosts.

294
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:28,520
I went to check just now,

295
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:30,080
that haunted seat...

296
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:31,480
I didn't see any bloodstains.

297
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:32,880
Of course you didn't.

298
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:34,680
The blood's under the seat cover.

299
00:15:34,680 --> 00:15:36,680
Guys, where the hell is Sky?

300
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:42,000
What?

301
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,800
Why the hell are you up there?

302
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,040
I'm changing the light bulb.

303
00:15:45,040 --> 00:15:46,040
Get over here!

304
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:47,760
What?

305
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,000
This is scary.

306
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,080
Don't be scared.

307
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:52,720
I'll lead the chant.

308
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,400
Sabbe Satta...

309
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,040
Sabbe Satta...

310
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,600
Shuffle.

311
00:15:58,760 --> 00:15:59,760
Shuffle.

312
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,760
Shuffle, shuffle, shuffle.

313
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:03,760
Sky, we're not playing cards!

314
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:07,120
I'm freaking out, I'm messing up all the prayers.

315
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,680
Sky, do it again, nicely.

316
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:09,680
Sabbe Satta...

317
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:10,760
Sabbe Satta...

318
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:11,720
All living beings...

319
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:13,160
All living beings...

320
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,040
that are my friends...

321
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,680
What? It's our companions in suffering.

322
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:19,200
You know what, that's enough!

323
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:21,240
Are you guys really that scared?

324
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:23,520
How can we not be?

325
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:25,520
You see that seat over there?

326
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:30,240
There've been rumors, people say they've seen a man sitting there,

327
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,400
just a dark figure.

328
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:35,400
Thing is, that seat hasn't even been up for sale in ages.

329
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,920
I'm scared...

330
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:47,600
I'm not scared!

331
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,080
All-New!

332
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:50,400
How can you not be scared?

333
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:53,000
I wrote a ghost-scanning app, remember?

334
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,000
Here.

335
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:57,000
If this device detects a ghost,

336
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:01,000
it will make a beep sound.

337
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:03,040
Yes, just like that.

338
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:10,520
Hey, that means, this device's just detected a ghost?

339
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:13,200
I don't think so. Maybe the device is malfunctioned.

340
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:17,200
I'll change it into another beep sound.

341
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:23,280
That was loud and clear.

342
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:28,800
I can't take this any longer.

343
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:34,680
Why are they so scared?

344
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:37,880
There's nothing to be scared of.

345
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,480
I don't think this is working properly.

346
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:02,480
My app must be unstable.

347
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:16,240
You look beautiful.

348
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:20,240
I remember that you like tiger print outfits.

349
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:25,160
It's not the tiger print I like...

350
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:27,400
It's the tiger pouncing on me.

351
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:28,400
Oh.

352
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:32,760
Here's the money you lent me.

353
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:34,160
It's alright.

354
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:35,480
Keep that.

355
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:37,400
Please. You don't have to give it back to me.

356
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:38,920
- I feel bad for troubling you.
- It's really alright.

357
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:41,480
Then, the dinner is on me.

358
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:44,600
No, no. Listen to me carefully.

359
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:47,160
The fact that you came out to have dinner with me...

360
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:49,840
it already means a lot so whatever you want to eat, whatever you feel like doing,

361
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:52,160
or if there's anything you want, with me or anything at all,

362
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:54,240
just tell me. I'll make it happen. Everything.

363
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:57,280
You're sweet as always.

364
00:18:57,280 --> 00:19:00,560
I don't think so.

365
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:01,880
I think I got sweeter.

366
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:04,960
Would you like to taste it?

367
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:07,920
So how are you these days?

368
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:09,480
I'm alright.

369
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:10,880
How about you, Sua?

370
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:13,040
Are you still a yoga instructor?

371
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,520
Yes, I am.

372
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:16,240
But the situation isn't really good.

373
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:18,360
I invested so much into opening my shop...

374
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:19,640
but then it got shut down.

375
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:22,280
Now, I'm buried in debt,

376
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:24,040
working my ass off just to stay afloat.

377
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:25,840
And my mom...she's been in the hospital...

378
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,440
for two years now.

379
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,840
Wow, that sounds really rough.

380
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:30,800
Yeah...

381
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:34,080
and my aunt just went into the jungle and got bitten by a mosquito, right here.

382
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:37,360
Now, she's got elephantiasis. Her leg's huge.

383
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:40,320
And my uncle, he was eating Larb,

384
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,160
duck Larb...

385
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,360
he was talking too much so he choked.

386
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:45,560
He's in the ICU now.

387
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:49,120
I'm really struggling right now, you know.

388
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:51,000
Damn, that's unbelievably tragic.

389
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,760
It is tragic.

390
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:56,520
Alright, listen. Let me help you.

391
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:58,280
Here, take this.

392
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,840
Use it however you want.

393
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:02,160
It's my supplementary card.

394
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:06,160
Maybe it'll make things just a little easier for you.

395
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:11,040
This is a senior citizen welfare card...

396
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:15,040
Ah, sorry, I grabbed my dad's by mistake.

397
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:17,880
Wait, this one's the real deal. Go ahead, use it.

398
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:19,440
Please don't do this.

399
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:22,040
I don't feel right about it.

400
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:24,040
It's okay. It's really okay.

401
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:27,240
Don't think too much, okay?

402
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:31,880
How about tonight, we forget about all the sadness and just have fun?

403
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:34,840
I promise...

404
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:38,840
I won't let this tiger run back into the jungle again.

405
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:43,520
Shall we?

406
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:44,520
Let's go.

407
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,200
Chaba!

408
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:52,800
Huh?

409
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,560
I can't walk.

410
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:56,560
We're almost at that seat.

411
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:59,240
I watched a movie once...

412
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:01,760
and they said if we held our breaths, ghosts wouldn't be able to see us.

413
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:02,440
Really?

414
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:03,080
Yeah.

415
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:05,080
Okay, then, one, two, three...

416
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:13,200
Excuse me.

417
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,200
Who's just called me?

418
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,880
Would you like tea or coffee?

419
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,240
There's no one!

420
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:34,160
Or could it be...

421
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:36,840
a ghost?

422
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:43,640
I think so.

423
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:47,080
Hold your breath.

424
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:48,760
Hold your breath.

425
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:49,720
Hold your breath.

426
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:50,720
I'm off!

427
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,000
Sky!

428
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,840
Are you a ghost?

429
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:57,000
Are you a foreign ghost?

430
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:00,760
G.H.O...what's the next letter?

431
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:03,240
Sky, I can't spell it!

432
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:04,240
I'm scared of a foreign ghost!

433
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:10,640
Let me have coffee!

434
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:12,280
There's no coffee.

435
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:13,560
There's only tea.

436
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:14,280
You know...

437
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:17,400
Let me have coffee!

438
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,680
I don't have any coffee...

439
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,400
Let me have coffee!

440
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,280
You're drinking too much coffee that...

441
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:22,280
your breath stinks!

442
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:29,040
Sky!

443
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:30,680
Tid-Gift!

444
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:37,000
What's that?

445
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,000
Who peed? Damn it!

446
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,120
I did.

447
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:44,440
I'm scared!

448
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:49,400
So you couldn't hold it because you saw...

449
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:50,160
Yes.

450
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,680
G.H.R.O.Y.A...

451
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:53,680
Z.A.O.Y...ghost.

452
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:14,160
I'm really happy today...

453
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:16,880
and I'm so glad we got to see each other again.

454
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:18,880
I'm happy too.

455
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:23,880
You know, it reminds me of when we went to that military camp at Khao Chon Kai.

456
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:27,080
You took such good care of me.

457
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:32,160
Especially, during the long-distance march.

458
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:35,720
Exactly, I was complaining about my feet hurting, and you,

459
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:39,720
you gave me your sanitary pad to stuff into my combat boots.

460
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:43,080
It helped so much. I could walk better after that.

461
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:45,080
That's because I knew how it felt.

462
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:50,120
But the most memorable night had to be...

463
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:51,840
the one before we went home.

464
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:57,320
You snuck into my tent, remember?

465
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:01,240
I remember it like it was yesterday.

466
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:03,240
Because that night,

467
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:14,760
the two of us were squirming around so much,
the tent stakes popped out and went flying!

468
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:22,280
I've never forgotten about that.

469
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:26,760
But that night, that was the past.

470
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:32,280
Now I'd like to get to know the present you.

471
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:36,280
I'd like you to understand my flavor and rhythm a little more, if that's alright.

472
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:42,520
Chai, of course, it's alright. Why wouldn't it be?

473
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:45,360
You said it, don't take it back.

474
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,960
You guys got tricked by the ghost, didn't you?

475
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:02,960
Ugh, what nonsense!

476
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:05,440
I don't believe in any of that ghost crap.

477
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:07,440
I really don't.

478
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:11,440
I'm all science, logic, facts. I wasn't running away.

479
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:14,720
I ran out to help Chaba.

480
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:15,720
The cart wheel was stuck.

481
00:25:18,840 --> 00:25:20,840
Your hair looks cool, by the way.

482
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,360
Of course.

483
00:25:23,360 --> 00:25:24,880
But Tid-Gift is lucky.

484
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,680
The ghost wouldn't mess with you.

485
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,680
Wouldn't mess with me, my ass.

486
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:30,080
My hair stays flawless, that's all.

487
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:33,360
So what are we gonna do now?

488
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:35,360
It's about time we serve another meal.

489
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,600
I'm not going.

490
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:44,240
Let's play to see who's it.

491
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:45,600
Alright, let's do it.

492
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:46,600
Yeah, yeah.

493
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:48,920
I think that's fair.

494
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,480
One, two, three.

495
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:05,040
It's alright, guys.

496
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:05,560
Chill.

497
00:26:05,560 --> 00:26:06,640
Really.

498
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:09,000
I've been working with this airline for years.

499
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,560
There's nothing scary.

500
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:12,440
Never seen a ghost before.

501
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:13,800
Never.

502
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:14,880
Really, you're safe.

503
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,880
Trust me.

504
00:26:21,160 --> 00:26:23,160
You'll get haunted!

505
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:34,560
Hey, wasn't that a beep sound, All-New?

506
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:37,480
I think it's malfunctioned.

507
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:39,520
I'll turn it off.

508
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:44,800
Why the hell are you clawing at my arm?

509
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:46,520
Sorry, mate.

510
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,440
Didn't you say you'd turned off the device, All-New?

511
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:55,560
I did turn it off.

512
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:11,120
Don't haunt us, sir.

513
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:16,920
Hey, where did he go?

514
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,520
Sir...

515
00:27:32,520 --> 00:27:34,520
All-New, why would you call him?

516
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:36,560
Where is your seat?

517
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,800
Then, please remain seated.

518
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:44,480
Kindly avoid disappearing and reappearing suddenly...

519
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:46,480
it could startle the other passengers.

520
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:52,920
My app's just messed up.

521
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:55,400
And this guy in the black hoodie must be cosplaying to fool people.

522
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:56,400
Hang on a sec.

523
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,320
Hey, there's a tattoo.

524
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,320
Shit, where did he go?

525
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:05,960
That's definitely a ghost!

526
00:28:05,960 --> 00:28:06,960
I'm outta here!

527
00:28:26,560 --> 00:28:27,560
My app really works!

528
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:49,840
Oh no, a ghost!

529
00:28:51,080 --> 00:28:52,760
What ghost are you talking about, Kreetha?

530
00:28:52,760 --> 00:28:55,120
Would you just look at me? Dressed like this?

531
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:56,120
I'm drop-dead gorgeous.

532
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:59,280
Speaking of a ghost, I'm still terrified.

533
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,280
That's true.

534
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:01,320
Can I let this go now?

535
00:29:01,320 --> 00:29:01,640
Yeah.

536
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:02,640
Okay.

537
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:04,800
I'm still scared. Damn it!

538
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:06,240
True. Where the hell is Sky?

539
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:10,240
I think she's so scared that she got sick.

540
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:12,280
It's good that I'm not afraid of ghosts.

541
00:29:12,280 --> 00:29:14,920
You're not scared? You freakin' pissed yourself.

542
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:18,920
Well, that black hoodie still kept haunting me.

543
00:29:19,480 --> 00:29:20,480
You meant this hoodie?

544
00:29:22,360 --> 00:29:23,160
Yeah, that's the one.

545
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,160
Take it.

546
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,000
Gift, take it.

547
00:29:28,280 --> 00:29:29,240
Why would you give it back to me, Chaba?

548
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:30,240
Take it.

549
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:36,360
I don't want it. I'm scared.

550
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:38,160
Why would you bring the hoodie here for?

551
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:40,640
Well, All-New was the one who kept it.

552
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:41,640
And he gave it to me.

553
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:46,640
Chai, help me!

554
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:48,840
Hey, what's going on?

555
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:51,360
What is this?

556
